The Vita FPGA Architecture Emulator Subproject is a program designed to
emulate the Vita FPGA Architecture on non-FPGA computer chips.

If you want to bypass the abstraction layers and add the Vita FPGA
Architecture to your computer chips, then check out the VitaFPGAArch
folder instead.

If you want to emulate the Vita FPGA Architecture on top of a Vita FPGA
Architecture chip (which doesn't exist yet) or on top of another FPGA
Architecture chip, then check out the VitaFPGAArch folder instead.

The Vita FPGA Architecture Emulator Subproject currently supports using
a single x86_64 CPU core as its backend. However, if you would like to
contribute new backends, then you are welcome to do so, so long as you
agree that your contributions to the Vita FPGA Architecture Emulator
Subproject will be licensed under The VitaSet license.

A backend that would be welcome to see, would be a GPGPU backend.

You need to have enough memory and patience to run this program.
However, you can still quit the program at any time with Ctrl + C, but
all of your progress may be lost. Future backends can reduce the amount
of patience required with their increased performance.

The Vita FPGA Architecture Synthesizer Subproject is under development,
and is licensed under The VitaSet License.
